<% content_for :title, "Asking for Help Checklist - Get Better Support for Baldrick Boards" %>

<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <%= render 'shared/breadcrumbs', breadcrumbs: page_breadcrumbs('Home', 'Support', 'Asking for Help') %>

  <!-- Main Content Card -->
  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <%= render 'shared/page_header', title: 'The Asking for Help Checklist', subtitle: 'Get answers to your questions quicker with this handy checklist' %>

    <!-- Content Section -->
    <div class="px-8 py-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Asking for Help Checklist</h2>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
            If you are reading this, it means someone has sent you this link to help you get answers to your question quicker.
          </p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
            We know that with showtime looming it can be stressful when things go wrong, so here is a handy checklist for you to quickly run through and double check.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 mb-8">
            <div class="flex">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-400" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div class="ml-3">
                <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">
                  <strong>Quick Fix:</strong> Most issues can be resolved by following these simple steps. Try them before asking for help!
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- If the pixels are not doing what they should -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">If the pixels are not doing what they should</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              This is usually a channel overlap issue and easily sortable.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 mb-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700">
                <strong>Important:</strong> Make sure each of your controllers has Auto Layout Models and Auto Layout Size and if possible full xLights Control enabled. <em>If you are unable to do that, make sure all your controllers have separate channels and universes</em>
              </p>
            </div>

            <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">1</span>
                <span>Re-render the sequence</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">2</span>
                <span>In xLights on the controller tab, click 'output to lights' on each of your controllers and keep an eye on the bottom left that they all succeed (sometimes they can fail)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">3</span>
                <span>Then in xLights click FPP Connect and do an upload with <strong>UDP Out</strong> set to <em>ALL</em> on your main show controller</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">4</span>
                <span>Check that the channels in xLights match the channels in FPP and on the Baldrick8 controller</span>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- If the pixels are not outputting via FPP -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">If the pixels are not outputting via FPP</h3>
            
            <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">1</span>
                <span>Make sure test mode isn't enabled on the Baldrick8</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">2</span>
                <span>Check the E1.31 Outputs tab in FPP and ensure the I.P. address matches your controller IP address</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">3</span>
                <span>Check the E1.31 Outputs tab in FPP and ensure the channels match the ones in the xLights controller tab</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">4</span>
                <span>Enable test mode on FPP and look at the stats box on the Baldrick8 - is it receiving data?</span>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- If the pixels are not outputting via xLights -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">If the pixels are not outputting via xLights</h3>
            
            <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">1</span>
                <span>Make sure test mode isn't enabled on the Baldrick8</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">2</span>
                <span>Check the controller tab in xLights and ensure the I.P. address matches your controller IP address</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">3</span>
                <span>Push outputs to the controller and make sure it's successful</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-sm font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-0.5">4</span>
                <span>Enable test mode on FPP and look at the stats box on the Baldrick8 - is it receiving data?</span>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- That didn't help -->
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-6 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">That didn't help</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
              If the checklist didn't solve it, then it's time to ask for help. If you are going to post on the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/3626858730963141" target="_blank" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 underline">Baldrick Community Facebook Group</a>, then here are some things that are really helpful to include (and will almost certainly be asked for, so posting them now will get you help quicker):
            </p>

            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 border border-red-200">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Essential Information to Include</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>What is the issue you are having</strong> (be as detailed as possible)</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>What have you tried so far</strong></span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>What version of xLights, FPP &/or Baldrick8 firmware</strong> are you using</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>Please include screenshots</strong> of your xLights controller tab (with the Baldrick8 selected), your FPP e1.31 Outputs page & your xLights Models section</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>If possible, a photo of the controller</strong> wired up</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-red-500 mr-3 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <span><strong>A bit of info about your network setup!</strong></span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 mt-6">
              <div class="flex">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-400" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="ml-3">
                  <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700">
                    <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> These might seem like a pain in the arse to gather, but trust us, it will get you a solution quicker. There is no such thing as too much information.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Actions -->
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Ready to Get Help?</h3>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-600 mr-3" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path d="M13 6a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zM18 8a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM14 15a4 4 0 00-8 0v3h8v-3z"></path>
                </svg>
                Facebook Community
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Post your question with all the information from the checklist above for the fastest response.
              </p>
              <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/3626858730963141" target="_blank" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
                Join Community
              </a>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-purple-600 mr-3" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path d="M3 1a1 1 0 000 2h1.22l.305 1.222a.997.997 0 00.01.042l1.358 5.43-.893.892C3.74 11.846 4.632 14 6.414 14H15a1 1 0 000-2H6.414l1-1H14a1 1 0 00.894-.553l3-6A1 1 0 0017 3H6.28l-.31-1.243A1 1 0 005 1H3zM16 16.5a1.5 1.5 0 11-3 0 1.5 1.5 0 013 0zM6.5 18a1.5 1.5 0 100-3 1.5 1.5 0 000 3z"/>
                </svg>
                Hardware Support
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                For physical hardware issues, defects, or warranty claims, use our direct support form.
              </p>
              <a href="/support" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-purple-700 transition-colors">
                Contact Support
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

                      <!-- Additional Fun Stuff -->
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-gray-200">
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Additional Fun Stuff</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Before asking for help, check these resources as they might already contain the solution to your problem.
        </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Documentation</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>• <a href="/boards" class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-700">Board Documentation</a></li>
                  <li>• <a href="/fun-stuff/faq" class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-700">FAQ Section</a></li>
<li>• <a href="/fun-stuff/release-notes" class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-700">Release Notes</a></li>
                  
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h5 class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">External Fun Stuff</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>• xLights Documentation</li>
                  <li>• FPP Documentation</li>
                  <li>• YouTube Tutorials</li>
                  <li>• Community Videos</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
